Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 394 948 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19  As of today, a cumulative total of 394 948 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded. Case Data Province Total cases for 22 July 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 67818 17,2 Free State 12332 3,1 Gauteng 144582 36,6 KwaZulu-Natal 50521 12,8 Limpopo 5712 1,4 Mpumalanga 8286 2,1 North West 15073 3,8 Northern Cape 2727 0,7 Western Cape 87847 22,2 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 394948 100,0 Testing Data The total number of tests conducted to date is 2 585 474 with 48 553 new tests conducted since the last report Sector Total tested  New tested  Private 1 460 168 56% 28 117 58% Public 1 125 306 44% 20 436 42% Total 2 585 474  48 553  Reported Deaths and Recoveries Regrettably we report 572 new COVID-19 related deaths. This brings the cumulative number of deaths to 5 940. We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The number of recoveries currently stands at 229 175 which translates to a recovery rate of 58% The provincial breakdown is as follows: Province Deaths Recoveries Eastern Cape 1345 49938 Free State 62 1315 Gauteng 1156 77397 KwaZulu-Natal 477 18067 Limpopo 33 2518 Mpumalanga 52 3435 North West 48 3914 Northern Cape 15 1100 Western Cape 2752 71491 Total 5940 229175 Issued by Department of Health, 22 July 2020  